description:
When executing INSERT RETURNING, the result rows are retrieved correctly but the Ecto struct mapping fails. The struct fields (especially id, timestamps) come back as nil even though the database persists the data correctly.

Example:
- INSERT with RETURNING should return: %Job{id: 123, inserted_at: ~U[...], ...}
- Currently returns: %Job{id: nil, inserted_at: nil, ...}

Tests: Oban integration tests all fail due to this.

libSQL 3.45.1 has full window function support: OVER, PARTITION BY, ORDER BY, frame specifications (ROWS BETWEEN, RANGE BETWEEN). Currently works via fragments but could benefit from dedicated query helpers.

Desired API:
  from u in User,
    select: %{
      name: u.name,
      running_total: over(sum(u.amount), partition_by: u.category, order_by: u.date)
    }

Effort: 4-5 days.
